Date: Tue, 22 Feb 2000 22:04:07 -0500
From: Abramo Ottolenghi <ottolenghi.1@osu.edu>

In its edition of 22 Feb 2000 Le Monde corrects itself by stating that
there where only 23 cases of listeriosis with seven deaths and not 30 as
previously reported. According to authorities quoted by Le Monde the
outbreak started at the end of November, 1999 with no new cases until the
end of December, then a peak in mid January with the last case being
diagnosed on 6 Feb 2000.
--
