Date: Wed, 23 Feb 2000 11:07:00 +0100
From: Michel Rosenheim <michel.rosenheim@psl.ap-hop-paris.fr>

Don't worry, pork tongue is not (yet ?) part of french newborns diet, such
as red or white wine, goose fat liver, french bread better known as
"baguette" and so on.
Newborns acquire _Listeria_ infection from their mother, not from hands but
from their bloodstream. If you have some medical knowledge or some general
culture you probably remember that during his intrauterine life, a foetus
receive everything he needs from his mother's blood. Unfortunately, some
pathogens are able to cross the placenta and to infect the foetus,
resulting in abortion or delivery of a dead newborn or delivery of an
infected newborn. Don't worry, even French mothers
(and sometimes fathers) wash their hands. By the way, I am not sure that
posting mail offensive to a group of people or to a country is a good
practice.
--
Dr. Michel Rosenheim
Service de Sante Publique
